--- src/why.src	(working copy)
+++ src/why.src	(working copy)
@@ -0,0 +1,16 @@
+<h1>Why MonoDevelop?</h1>
+            <p>Today Linux is lacking good development tools. There are
+some good
+efforts, but we wanted something that would work fine with C#. </p>
+            <p>There were various efforts to create a Gtk# based
+development
+environment (Scaffold, Sugar, torkar's, csharp-develop) and a couple of
+others. </p>
+            <p>We knew that SharpDevelop was the best thing out there
+for C# and we
+initially wanted to get the intellisense widget ported, then we would
+deffer to others the creation of the IDE. </p>
+            <p>But soon the hackers realized that it was relatively
+easy to port the
+whole thing, and the process started. </p>
+			<p>NB. This is an extract from a posting to the MonoDevelop-List, by Miguel de Incaza on 08 Jan 2004.</p>
